00:29:44.778 --> 00:29:46.569
Soviet Union at the time.
 

00:29:46.569 --> 00:29:48.588
That was 1985 to 1998.
 

00:29:48.588 --> 00:29:51.440
From 1998 to 2007,
again the latest data,

00:29:51.440 --> 00:29:54.679
16 nations liberalized their
abortion laws and two

00:29:54.679 --> 00:29:58.182
territories and one state in
Australia liberalized its

00:29:58.182 --> 00:30:02.210
abortion laws,
and in Mexico I mentioned.

00:30:02.210 --> 00:30:07.537
Mexico City has now made
abortion in the first 12 weeks

00:30:07.537 --> 00:30:11.261
legal and that was in 19--
2007 I believe,

00:30:11.261 --> 00:30:14.599
and than a few states in Mexico
has followed that,

00:30:14.599 --> 00:30:17.818
so Mexico is now a split place.
 

00:30:17.818 --> 00:30:24.740
In this 1998 to 2007 time frame
El Salvador and Nicaragua,

00:30:24.740 --> 00:30:28.080
which already had a very
restrictive abortion laws went

00:30:28.080 --> 00:30:30.144
to absolute,
under no circumstances,

00:30:30.144 --> 00:30:33.311
abortion is totally--
no rape, no death--health of

00:30:33.311 --> 00:30:38.710
the mother,
no exceptions in Nicaragua and

00:30:38.710 --> 00:30:40.630
El Salvador.
 

00:30:40.630 --> 00:30:43.816
In contrast to the safety of
legal abortion,

00:30:43.816 --> 00:30:47.891
where abortions--when it's
legal it's almost always in a

00:30:47.891 --> 00:30:50.038
proper medical situation.
 

00:30:50.038 --> 00:30:54.208
When it's illegal,
it's an extremely dangerous

00:30:54.208 --> 00:30:55.318
procedure.
 

00:30:55.318 --> 00:31:00.406
There's something like 67,000
abortion related deaths a year

00:31:00.406 --> 00:31:04.718
and that leaves 220,000,
a quarter million children

00:31:04.718 --> 00:31:06.960
without their mothers.
 

00:31:06.960 --> 00:31:09.130
As you may know,
when it's illegal,

00:31:09.130 --> 00:31:15.528
the main procedure is inserting
something up the uterus and

00:31:15.528 --> 00:31:21.816
scraping around to try to
dislodge the endometrium and the

00:31:21.816 --> 00:31:22.920
fetus.
 

00:31:22.920 --> 00:31:25.747
Well, if you're scraping around
in there with a pointed stick or

00:31:25.747 --> 00:31:28.375
a hangar or something,
you're liable to puncture the

00:31:28.375 --> 00:31:31.127
uterine wall and make a hole
between the inside of the

00:31:31.127 --> 00:31:32.932
uterus,
which is open through the

00:31:32.932 --> 00:31:36.154
vaginal canal to the outside,
and the peritoneal cavity,

00:31:36.154 --> 00:31:40.133
the inside of your body and so
infection gets through that and

00:31:40.133 --> 00:31:43.423
so the main route isn't--
the main reason why

00:31:43.423 --> 00:31:48.272
abortion--illegal abortion is so
dangerous is that non-sterility

00:31:48.272 --> 00:31:51.200
of whatever it is that's
inserted,

00:31:51.200 --> 00:31:56.170
plus it's pointed usually,
and they break right through

00:31:56.170 --> 00:31:57.920
the uterine wall.
 

00:31:57.920 --> 00:32:00.875
In addition,
you may know that the fallopian

00:32:00.875 --> 00:32:05.068
tube is open into the peritoneal
cavity because the ovary,

00:32:05.068 --> 00:32:08.556
which releases the egg is--it
sits right on top of the

00:32:08.556 --> 00:32:12.306
fallopian tube and the egg is
released into the peritoneal

00:32:12.306 --> 00:32:14.837
space,
the body fluid here and it's

00:32:14.837 --> 00:32:18.843
supposed to drop down into the
fallopian tube and cilia push it

00:32:18.843 --> 00:32:19.358
down.
 

00:32:19.358 --> 00:32:23.519
That's an opening so if you get
something unsterile into the

00:32:23.519 --> 00:32:27.749
womb and then the bacteria can
swim upstream and get into the

00:32:27.749 --> 00:32:32.049
body and then you're into sepsis
and you very likely die.

00:32:36.048 --> 00:32:43.109
It's a very dangerous procedure
when done not properly.

00:32:47.118 --> 00:32:51.612
There are very good statistics
showing that the main

00:32:51.612 --> 00:32:56.721
determinant of the maternal
death rate from abortion is its

00:32:56.721 --> 00:32:58.220
legal status.
 

00:33:01.710 --> 00:33:04.440
Here again, although I don't
think I showed this slide,

00:33:04.440 --> 00:33:07.940
so here is places where
abortion is legal,

00:33:07.940 --> 00:33:10.695
here's the abortion rate,
this goes back to saying that

00:33:10.695 --> 00:33:13.808
the legal situation doesn't
determine the rate of abortion.

00:33:13.808 --> 00:33:20.030
Here are various abortion legal
places and the rate is about 6

00:33:20.030 --> 00:33:23.585
to 26,
and here it's illegal and you

00:33:23.585 --> 00:33:28.978
have the range of 23 to 52,
so ballpark double or triple

00:33:28.978 --> 00:33:30.859
this rate,
so it's illegal.

00:33:30.859 --> 00:33:32.759
These are all South America.
 

00:33:32.759 --> 00:33:36.198
This is all Europe,
Japan, Australia,

00:33:36.198 --> 00:33:40.210
United States,
very developed countries.

00:33:40.210 --> 00:33:43.288
Countries that are partially
developed shall we say.

00:33:43.288 --> 00:33:49.212
The illegality correlates with
the abortion rate but it's

00:33:49.212 --> 00:33:54.766
almost certainly not the cause,
certainly being illegal is not

00:33:54.766 --> 00:33:57.048
causing these high abortion
rates.

00:33:57.048 --> 00:34:01.521
Now when you go over and look
at the maternal deaths you see

00:34:01.521 --> 00:34:04.519
that there are ten,
the developed regions have an

00:34:04.519 --> 00:34:07.412
average of ten,
whereas in Latin America you

00:34:07.412 --> 00:34:11.670
have up in the 100 and 200,
and even up to 300 range.

00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:14.590
You go to Africa it's 650.
 

00:34:14.590 --> 00:34:18.778
There the illegality really
does make a difference in the

00:34:18.778 --> 00:34:23.143
maternal death rate,
that's the dominant effect of

00:34:23.143 --> 00:34:27.027
making something illegal is--
doesn't change the abortion

00:34:27.027 --> 00:34:28.730
rate and we have a number of
examples,

00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:33.666
but it changes the maternal
death rate very,

00:34:33.666 --> 00:34:35.389
very clearly.
 

00:34:35.389 --> 00:34:39.045
The most extreme example of
this and the clearest example of

00:34:39.045 --> 00:34:40.469
this is from Romania.
 

00:34:40.469 --> 00:34:48.173
Romania had during--after World
War II when it was a Soviet

00:34:48.173 --> 00:34:51.123
puppet state,
as I told you,

00:34:51.123 --> 00:34:53.768
the abortion rate was
extraordinarily high,

00:34:53.768 --> 00:34:56.650
like four abortions for every
one live birth.

00:34:56.650 --> 00:35:01.619
Because--well they had a
dictator then,

00:35:01.619 --> 00:35:04.177
Nicolai Ceausescu,
who you've undoubtedly have

00:35:04.177 --> 00:35:06.085
heard of,
and he decided that for the

00:35:06.085 --> 00:35:08.719
glory of greater Romania there
should be more Romanians,

00:35:08.719 --> 00:35:13.659
he wanted a big strong state,
so he went on a pronatalist

00:35:13.659 --> 00:35:14.630
campaign.
 

00:35:14.630 --> 00:35:17.327
Abortion was immediately
criminalized,

00:35:17.327 --> 00:35:21.485
contraceptives became very hard
to get hard, they wouldn't

00:35:21.485 --> 00:35:24.840
import them, they didn't
manufacture them.

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:29.795
So what he did was that all
women between 18 and 45 were

00:35:29.795 --> 00:35:33.985
rounded up at their workplace,
remember this is a socialist

00:35:33.985 --> 00:35:35.679
state so almost all the women
worked,

00:35:35.679 --> 00:35:37.559
they were rounded up at their
workplace,

00:35:37.559 --> 00:35:40.340
and subjected to a
gynecological examination.

00:35:40.340 --> 00:35:44.057
If they were not
pregnant they had to explain to

00:35:44.057 --> 00:35:46.739
the government why they were not
pregnant.

00:35:46.739 --> 00:35:51.670
It was about as intrusive a
pronatalist campaign as you can

00:35:51.670 --> 00:35:52.518
imagine.
 

00:35:52.518 --> 00:35:58.148
It's somewhat the mirror image
of China's anti-birth campaign,

00:35:58.148 --> 00:36:01.469
and Romania had the plus
campaign.

00:36:01.469 --> 00:36:05.284
Anyway, what happened
immediately--so previously 80%

00:36:05.284 --> 00:36:09.396
of pregnancies had been
ending--had been terminated with

00:36:09.396 --> 00:36:10.369
abortion.
 

00:36:10.369 --> 00:36:12.599
Abortion disappears,
and was legal,

00:36:12.599 --> 00:36:15.945
abortion had been legal,
and boom the birthrate does

00:36:15.945 --> 00:36:18.775
indeed go up;
nothing like by a factor of

00:36:18.775 --> 00:36:22.269
five but something like a factor
two as I remember but I

00:36:22.269 --> 00:36:24.050
want--should--check that.
 

00:36:24.050 --> 00:36:27.210
Then, very rapidly,
women set up networks of

00:36:27.210 --> 00:36:31.621
illegal abortion providers and
the birth rate goes up and the

00:36:31.621 --> 00:36:36.103
birth rate comes back down and
it ends up somewhat higher than

00:36:36.103 --> 00:36:42.518
it had been beforehand,
but not enormously higher.

00:36:42.518 --> 00:36:45.920
The maternal death rate is what
changed.

00:36:45.920 --> 00:36:50.518
It rose to 200 per 100,000 live
births, from a number in a

00:36:50.518 --> 00:36:54.550
developed country that was
something in the tens or

00:36:54.550 --> 00:36:55.599
twenties.
 

00:36:55.599 --> 00:37:00.500
It ranged up to ten times that
amount.

00:37:00.500 --> 00:37:03.690
The infant mortality rate,
because these mothers didn't

00:37:03.690 --> 00:37:06.922
want these children,
presumably, the infant

00:37:06.922 --> 00:37:11.179
mortality rate rose to 83 deaths
per 1,000 from--

00:37:11.179 --> 00:37:15.878
Japan's rate is 4.8,
the U.S.

00:37:15.878 --> 00:37:20.409
is 8.9, so it rose to 83.
 

00:37:20.409 --> 00:37:23.699
So again, something like a ten
times increase in infant

00:37:23.699 --> 00:37:24.429
mortality.
 

00:37:24.429 --> 00:37:28.047
The main effect of
de-legalizing abortion was a

00:37:28.047 --> 00:37:32.923
temporary rise in the number of
births but a long term increase

00:37:32.923 --> 00:37:36.699
in maternal mortality and infant
mortality,

00:37:36.699 --> 00:37:38.699
a massive increase.
 

00:37:38.699 --> 00:37:43.722
By the time abortion--of course
when they got free of the

00:37:43.722 --> 00:37:46.846
dictator--
it was legalized again and

00:37:46.846 --> 00:37:49.615
then, by that time,
things had come back a little

00:37:49.615 --> 00:37:50.039
to normal.
 

00:37:50.039 --> 00:37:51.630
But still, the maternal death
rate,

00:37:51.630 --> 00:37:53.139
as soon as they legalized
abortion,

00:37:53.139 --> 00:37:56.030
the maternal death rate dropped
by a factor three,

00:37:56.030 --> 00:37:58.980
so that's Romania's nice
example.

00:37:58.980 --> 00:38:01.164
In South Africa,
more recently,

00:38:01.164 --> 00:38:04.659
this was in the late 1960s,
the Romania story.

00:38:04.659 --> 00:38:09.045
In South Africa the abortion
law was liberalized and the

00:38:09.045 --> 00:38:14.309
incidence of maternal infection
due to abortion dropped in half.

00:38:14.309 --> 00:38:20.141
In all cases the major effect
of making abortion illegal is an

00:38:20.141 --> 00:38:22.820
increase in complications.
 

00:38:22.820 --> 00:38:27.161
You don't change the abortion
rate, but medical complications,

00:38:27.161 --> 00:38:30.579
death of the mother,
and death of the infants.

00:38:33.630 --> 00:38:36.521
The fundamental--we've been
going through things that are

00:38:36.521 --> 00:38:38.588
not the cause of the high
abortion rates,

00:38:38.588 --> 00:38:41.119
it's not the religion,
it's not the legality.

00:38:41.119 --> 00:38:45.409
The fundamental causes of--kind
of obvious--is unintended

00:38:45.409 --> 00:38:46.329
pregnancy.
 

00:38:46.329 --> 00:38:49.623
You may remember that
these--there are very high rates

00:38:49.623 --> 00:38:51.239
of unintended pregnancy.
 

00:38:51.239 --> 00:38:55.119
--Here is a comparison of two
regions,

00:38:55.119 --> 00:38:58.599
almost all legal in the
developed countries and in

00:38:58.599 --> 00:39:02.574
almost all of Africa it's
illegal and the death rate's an

00:39:02.574 --> 00:39:06.739
enormous,
enormous difference there.

00:39:06.739 --> 00:39:10.349
You may remember these
statistics, just to refresh your

00:39:10.349 --> 00:39:12.690
memory, about unwanted
fertility.

00:39:12.690 --> 00:39:17.659
This is 71% of living women
want to stop having children.

00:39:17.659 --> 00:39:21.289
Yet, as I showed you before,
they have more--

00:39:21.289 --> 00:39:23.650
they continue to have children
because they're not using

00:39:23.650 --> 00:39:25.931
contraception,
they don't have enough

00:39:25.931 --> 00:39:26.989
contraception.
 

00:39:26.989 --> 00:39:28.230
That's Bolivia.
 

00:39:28.230 --> 00:39:31.268
This is from the previous
lecture around the world,

00:39:31.268 --> 00:39:34.150
remember this is the line where
people--

00:39:34.150 --> 00:39:37.230
this is how many children
people are having,

00:39:37.230 --> 00:39:40.079
this is how many they want,
this is the line where they're

00:39:40.079 --> 00:39:40.480
equal.
 

00:39:40.480 --> 00:39:42.559
All countries,
all developing countries are

00:39:42.559 --> 00:39:44.440
having more children than they
want.

00:39:44.440 --> 00:39:48.409
There's a large amount of unmet
need in the world.

00:39:48.409 --> 00:39:52.059
The estimate for the world is
108 million women.

00:39:56.190 --> 00:40:00.239
Since there's an unmet need,
these women who don't want to

00:40:00.239 --> 00:40:04.291
have more children yet do,
that results in some 51 million

00:40:04.291 --> 00:40:06.210
unintended pregnancies.
 

00:40:06.210 --> 00:40:10.846
Of those using contraception,
another 25 million happen as a

00:40:10.846 --> 00:40:13.911
result of incorrect,
inconsistent use of

00:40:13.911 --> 00:40:16.739
contraception or method failure.
 

00:40:16.739 --> 00:40:22.530
You have something like 80
million unwanted pregnancies.

00:40:22.530 --> 00:40:27.757
In the world there are 210
million pregnancies annually,

00:40:27.757 --> 00:40:31.369
and about 40% of them are
unplanned.

00:40:31.369 --> 00:40:34.154
About a quarter of--We know,
from a lot of places,

00:40:34.154 --> 00:40:37.449
that when there's an unplanned
pregnancy about a quarter of

00:40:37.449 --> 00:40:38.869
them end in abortion.
 

00:40:38.869 --> 00:40:46.014
The main sequence is:
unwanted pregnancy and then

00:40:46.014 --> 00:40:49.139
high abortion rate.
 

00:40:49.139 --> 00:40:54.862
Most unintended pregnancies in
the world--most unintended

00:40:54.862 --> 00:40:59.360
pregnancies are in the developed
counties.

00:40:59.360 --> 00:41:00.742
So there's a difference here
between developed and

00:41:00.742 --> 00:41:01.420
undeveloped countries.
 

00:41:01.420 --> 00:41:05.943
Contraception is very available
and highly used in the developed

00:41:05.943 --> 00:41:08.637
world,
so in the developed world most

00:41:08.637 --> 00:41:11.780
unintended pregnancies are
people who are using

00:41:11.780 --> 00:41:15.184
contraception,
and using it fairly accurately,

00:41:15.184 --> 00:41:20.039
but there's a method failure,
the contraception just fails.

00:41:20.039 --> 00:41:25.460
You have to remember that a
woman is fertile for say 30

00:41:25.460 --> 00:41:27.469
years of her life.
 

00:41:27.469 --> 00:41:31.088
She has 12 monthly cycles in a
year, a little bit more

00:41:31.088 --> 00:41:35.047
actually, a cycle is 28 days in
principle, but that's close

00:41:35.047 --> 00:41:35.800
enough.
 

00:41:35.800 --> 00:41:40.751
In order to not have an
unintended pregnancy her

00:41:40.751 --> 00:41:45.599
contraception must be perfect
for 30 years,

00:41:45.599 --> 00:41:48.190
12 cycles a year,
that's an awful lot to expect

00:41:48.190 --> 00:41:52.469
of a contraceptive,
and contraceptives are just not

00:41:52.469 --> 00:41:53.550
that good.
 

00:41:53.550 --> 00:41:57.659
So, in developed countries
also, the main reason for

00:41:57.659 --> 00:42:01.447
unintended pregnancy,
it's very heavily--married

00:42:01.447 --> 00:42:04.510
women who are using
contraception.

00:42:04.510 --> 00:42:06.802
They usually have several
children already,

00:42:06.802 --> 00:42:08.440
and the contraception fails.
 

00:42:08.440 --> 00:42:12.260
That's the main reason in
developed countries.

00:42:12.260 --> 00:42:17.222
In developing countries where
contraception use is less

00:42:17.222 --> 00:42:22.460
prevalent, the main reason is
non-use of contraception.

00:42:25.789 --> 00:42:27.884
There is a very strong
relationship between

00:42:27.884 --> 00:42:29.329
contraception and abortion.
 

00:42:29.329 --> 00:42:32.871
-- So, we have a country,
most countries,

00:42:32.871 --> 00:42:36.518
with this unmet need;
women, before you start

00:42:36.518 --> 00:42:39.739
collecting statistics,
want fewer children than

00:42:39.739 --> 00:42:42.679
they're having but it's not a
big deal.

00:42:42.679 --> 00:42:45.572
Then something changes,
could be a mechanism that we've

00:42:45.572 --> 00:42:47.929
discussed the reasons of
cultural change,

00:42:47.929 --> 00:42:49.586
and economic change,
or whatever,

00:42:49.586 --> 00:42:52.539
and people really start wanting
to have fewer children.

00:42:52.539 --> 00:42:56.463
This happened around 1964 in
Korea and you read--and I gave

00:42:56.463 --> 00:43:00.659
you one of the stories about how
an example of how this happens

00:43:00.659 --> 00:43:01.539
in Korea.
 

00:43:01.539 --> 00:43:05.036
What happens is as women--as
the whole culture changes from

00:43:05.036 --> 00:43:08.833
wanting sort of the maximum rate
of fertility to wanting a lower

00:43:08.833 --> 00:43:12.271
rate of fertility,
the contraception--the abortion

00:43:12.271 --> 00:43:16.373
rate takes off first because in
all these countries abortion is

00:43:16.373 --> 00:43:18.775
the traditional method,
the women know it,

00:43:18.775 --> 00:43:20.179
and are moderately comfortable
with it,

00:43:20.179 --> 00:43:23.489
so you see first the abortion
rate starts going up.

00:43:23.489 --> 00:43:26.724
Then, with a short lag,
the contraception rate goes up,

00:43:26.724 --> 00:43:29.721
because all the countries
establish national family

00:43:29.721 --> 00:43:31.039
planning programs.
 

00:43:31.039 --> 00:43:37.690
What happens is people use more
abortion,

00:43:37.690 --> 00:43:40.735
use more contraception,
so they're reducing their

00:43:40.735 --> 00:43:43.443
fertility,
but the rate of drop of desired

00:43:43.443 --> 00:43:46.969
fertility can be so fast that
even the sum of contraception

00:43:46.969 --> 00:43:49.340
and abortion can't keep up with
it,

00:43:49.340 --> 00:43:51.139
so both rates keep rising.
 

00:43:51.139 --> 00:43:54.260
Eventually you peak.
 

00:43:54.260 --> 00:43:57.230
Abortion peaks and starts
falling down,

00:43:57.230 --> 00:43:59.809
contraception continues upward.
 

00:43:59.809 --> 00:44:04.192
This is the time when the
demand to have less fertility is

00:44:04.192 --> 00:44:07.730
more than either method alone
can cope with.

00:44:07.730 --> 00:44:12.159
Eventually women--and abortion
is easier because the post--

00:44:12.159 --> 00:44:17.543
it's an after the fact method,
but eventually women learn to

00:44:17.543 --> 00:44:21.760
use contraception--
learn to use it and learn to

00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:26.690
use it properly and so then the
abortion rate declines as the

00:44:26.690 --> 00:44:31.539
contraception rate continues on
up to very high levels,

00:44:31.539 --> 00:44:34.295
and most of the difference here
is women who want to get

00:44:34.295 --> 00:44:35.500
pregnant or something.
 

00:44:35.500 --> 00:44:36.960
You have this trade off.
 

00:44:36.960 --> 00:44:40.590
You have, in an early stage,
both of them rise together and

00:44:40.590 --> 00:44:43.659
at a later stage they do very
divergent things.

00:44:43.659 --> 00:44:49.059
You'll see when you get a
polemicized discussion of this,

00:44:49.059 --> 00:44:52.099
what you'd hear is right to
life people say,

00:44:52.099 --> 00:44:54.753
'contraception is no good,
abortion rises with

00:44:54.753 --> 00:44:57.998
contraception' and they use
statistics from this half on

00:44:57.998 --> 00:44:58.530
down.
 

00:44:58.530 --> 00:45:01.157
People who are pro-choice say
'no, no, no or are

00:45:01.157 --> 00:45:04.065
pro-contraception no,
no, no it goes this way and the

00:45:04.065 --> 00:45:05.800
use this half of the graph.
 

00:45:05.800 --> 00:45:08.199
But you get both of these
things.

00:45:08.199 --> 00:45:10.179
Korea is one example.
 

00:45:10.179 --> 00:45:14.722
Here is another example of the
relationship between

00:45:14.722 --> 00:45:18.630
contraception and abortion in
Bangladesh.

00:45:18.630 --> 00:45:22.400
Here is--remember Matlab--you
read about Matlab where they

00:45:22.400 --> 00:45:26.106
chose some villages and got a
very strong family planning

00:45:26.106 --> 00:45:30.009
program and then other villages
which they left as a control

00:45:30.009 --> 00:45:30.869
region.
 

00:45:30.869 --> 00:45:32.996
They had family planning
because they had the government

00:45:32.996 --> 00:45:35.240
program, but the government
program wasn't any near as good

00:45:35.240 --> 00:45:36.480
as the intervention program.
 

00:45:36.480 --> 00:45:40.280
Here's the control region and a
lot to see here.

00:45:40.280 --> 00:45:45.920
First of all this is desired
fertility and that starts at

00:45:45.920 --> 00:45:51.460
this level and drops down to
somewhat more than half;

00:45:51.460 --> 00:45:55.434
desired fertility in the Matlab
region starts at about the same

00:45:55.434 --> 00:45:58.000
level and falls about the same
amount.

00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:00.501
The difference between the two
regions is not desired

00:46:00.501 --> 00:46:01.079
fertility.
 

00:46:01.079 --> 00:46:05.989
The actual fertility rate drops
here, starts higher and drops a

00:46:05.989 --> 00:46:09.630
little faster here,
so that it ends up not very

00:46:09.630 --> 00:46:10.739
different.
 

00:46:10.739 --> 00:46:14.224
Again, the difference is not
the actual amount of fertility,

00:46:14.224 --> 00:46:17.295
which the number of births
isn't enormously different

00:46:17.295 --> 00:46:18.949
between the two regions.
 

00:46:18.949 --> 00:46:23.909
In Matlab--in the experimental
region,

00:46:23.909 --> 00:46:26.110
the region where they had the
good program,

00:46:26.110 --> 00:46:29.766
the contraceptive prevalence
goes very high or goes rapidly

00:46:29.766 --> 00:46:32.099
very high from something like
30%,

00:46:32.099 --> 00:46:33.768
more than doubles to 70%.
 

00:46:33.768 --> 00:46:39.849
Whereas, in the other--in the
non-control region you have--

00:46:39.849 --> 00:46:44.039
it starts much lower--this
rises very rapidly,

00:46:44.039 --> 00:46:46.070
this doesn't change at all for
a number of years,

00:46:46.070 --> 00:46:48.242
then the government--actually
the government improves its

00:46:48.242 --> 00:46:50.768
program,
it jumps up a little bit.

00:46:50.768 --> 00:46:53.867
So it's the contraceptive,
this is a really big

00:46:53.867 --> 00:46:57.311
difference,
the contraceptive prevalence is

00:46:57.311 --> 00:47:02.639
much lower in the control region
than in the experimental region.

00:47:02.639 --> 00:47:05.650
The result is:
here's the abortion ratio in

00:47:05.650 --> 00:47:09.378
the region where the
contraceptive prevalence is very

00:47:09.378 --> 00:47:13.608
high and here the abortion ratio
goes crazy where they don't

00:47:13.608 --> 00:47:16.963
have--
they're not using contraception

00:47:16.963 --> 00:47:18.010
efficiently.
 

00:47:18.010 --> 00:47:20.670
Again here you can see in those
two regions the same country,

00:47:20.670 --> 00:47:22.710
the same time,
neighboring villages,

00:47:22.710 --> 00:47:28.980
neighboring districts that
the--there's this tradeoff.

00:47:28.980 --> 00:47:31.900
They either use contraception
or they use abortion.

00:47:31.900 --> 00:47:35.170
Both places,
they're wanting fewer children

00:47:35.170 --> 00:47:38.284
as time goes on,
but in one case they use

00:47:38.284 --> 00:47:42.800
contraception and in the other
case they use abortion.

00:47:42.800 --> 00:47:46.340
Here's another example of this,
rather different in Shanghai.

00:47:46.340 --> 00:47:50.409
This is a more complicated,
somewhat interesting case.

00:47:50.409 --> 00:47:54.268
This is the one-child policy
comes in.

00:47:54.268 --> 00:47:57.784
They're only allowed one child,
so they have that child and

00:47:57.784 --> 00:48:01.360
then they try to do something to
avoid the second child,

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:06.688
and what they use is
contraceptive methods and they

00:48:06.688 --> 00:48:10.322
don't work,
they start with very--let me

00:48:10.322 --> 00:48:12.159
get this straight here.
 

00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:19.123
They start with a low use of
IUD which is a really secure

00:48:19.123 --> 00:48:23.309
method of contraception and the
abortion rate is very high and

00:48:23.309 --> 00:48:27.358
they rather rapidly learn that
IUD is the only really secure

00:48:27.358 --> 00:48:31.409
way of not getting pregnant and
then the abortion rate falls

00:48:31.409 --> 00:48:34.005
down,
so it's another rather

00:48:34.005 --> 00:48:38.391
different situation in which
again the abortion rate and the

00:48:38.391 --> 00:48:43.150
effective contraceptive rate are
mirror images of each other.

00:48:43.150 --> 00:48:47.956
When you have a high rate of
effective contraception you have

00:48:47.956 --> 00:48:49.960
a low rate of abortion.
 

00:48:59.239 --> 00:49:02.190
Latin America shows this same
pattern.

00:49:02.190 --> 00:49:06.710
In Latin America abortions have
been practiced for centuries.

00:49:06.710 --> 00:49:10.079
It was certainly practiced by
the Incas and the Aztecs.

00:49:10.079 --> 00:49:14.130
In 1551 the Bishop of Venezuela
reported to the King of Spain

00:49:14.130 --> 00:49:18.519
that the natives did not want
their children to become slaves,

00:49:18.519 --> 00:49:21.380
so they aborted them, 1551.
 

00:49:21.380 --> 00:49:25.829
Chile has very good medical
statistics.

00:49:25.829 --> 00:49:30.025
At the beginning of Chile's
fertility transition in the

00:49:30.025 --> 00:49:34.375
1960s 23% of Chilean women
voluntarily admitted to having

00:49:34.375 --> 00:49:36.239
an induced abortion.
 

00:49:36.239 --> 00:49:39.351
Again, remember Chile is very
heavily a Catholic country and

00:49:39.351 --> 00:49:42.516
this is not really delving into
medical records or making any

00:49:42.516 --> 00:49:43.360
corrections.
 

00:49:43.360 --> 00:49:45.018
This is just asking the women,
Have you had an abortion?'

00:49:45.018 --> 00:49:47.760
and a quarter of them say,
yes I've had an abortion.

00:49:47.760 --> 00:49:52.474
Not only did they have an
abortion but most of them had

00:49:52.474 --> 00:49:55.530
more than one abortion,
up to three,

00:49:55.530 --> 00:50:00.070
8.4% of the women had more than
seven abortions.

00:50:00.070 --> 00:50:04.469
This is early on.
 

00:50:04.469 --> 00:50:08.260
Ten years later in the 1970s
now it's--

00:50:08.260 --> 00:50:12.119
where women are really into
their fertility decline,

00:50:12.119 --> 00:50:15.442
they don't want the children,
the average woman has almost

00:50:15.442 --> 00:50:21.079
three abortions,
lifetime, so that goes up.

00:50:21.079 --> 00:50:24.222
Again, those are the openly
admitted numbers and the real

00:50:24.222 --> 00:50:26.300
numbers must have been much
higher.

00:50:26.300 --> 00:50:30.268
Again, as in elsewhere,
in Chile almost all the women

00:50:30.268 --> 00:50:33.197
were married,
almost all middle class women,

00:50:33.197 --> 00:50:36.099
and they already had had four
to six pregnancies,

00:50:36.099 --> 00:50:39.949
they already had children,
and experience with pregnancy.

00:50:39.949 --> 00:50:43.623
In terms of socioeconomic
levels, middle class women had

00:50:43.623 --> 00:50:46.429
more abortions than working
class women.

00:50:46.429 --> 00:50:51.922
Married women had a greater
abortion rate than those living

00:50:51.922 --> 00:50:56.460
in temporary unions,
and in all--through all this

00:50:56.460 --> 00:51:01.264
time abortion was completely
illegal in Chile and it still

00:51:01.264 --> 00:51:01.768
is.
 

00:51:01.768 --> 00:51:08.139
Going next door to Peru,
in Lima in the 1970s,

00:51:08.139 --> 00:51:10.268
again the time when the
fertility was going down,

00:51:10.268 --> 00:51:13.210
when people were wanting fewer
children in Peru,

00:51:13.210 --> 00:51:16.550
the yearly increase in the
abortion rate was 24%,

00:51:16.550 --> 00:51:20.320
every year there was a 24%
increase in abortion.

00:51:20.320 --> 00:51:24.280
In any given year a quarter to
a third of the reproductive age

00:51:24.280 --> 00:51:27.509
women would have abortions,
that's one out four,

00:51:27.509 --> 00:51:31.219
one out of three women every
year would have an abortion.

00:51:34.268 --> 00:51:39.882
Again, it's in this--the really
high abortion rates are when

00:51:39.882 --> 00:51:42.967
women are--
or families are starting to

00:51:42.967 --> 00:51:47.072
want fewer children and haven't
yet really figured out how to

00:51:47.072 --> 00:51:48.510
use contraception.
 

00:51:48.510 --> 00:51:52.780
In contemporary Latin America
abortion,

00:51:52.780 --> 00:51:55.480
although it's illegal almost
everywhere and it's almost

00:51:55.480 --> 00:51:59.699
universally a Catholic place,
abortion is very widespread.

00:51:59.699 --> 00:52:04.735
Latin America as a whole has 1
abortion for every 2 live

00:52:04.735 --> 00:52:07.673
births;
remember worldwide and in the

00:52:07.673 --> 00:52:07.965
U.S.
 

00:52:07.965 --> 00:52:11.246
it's 1 per 3.2,
Latin American has 1 for every

00:52:11.246 --> 00:52:12.559
2 live births.
 

00:52:12.559 --> 00:52:15.978
Eventually there's a
generational change and the

00:52:15.978 --> 00:52:19.688
younger women start using
contraception and then the

00:52:19.688 --> 00:52:22.090
abortion rate starts to fall.
 

00:52:32.440 --> 00:52:38.213
The Philippines,
another example--in the

00:52:38.213 --> 00:52:45.764
Philippines have a very
interesting situation of the

00:52:45.764 --> 00:52:47.690
politics.
 

00:52:47.690 --> 00:52:51.172
There's a strong
inter-relationship between the

00:52:51.172 --> 00:52:54.503
politics of the country,
the Catholic Church,

00:52:54.503 --> 00:52:57.760
and the citizen's use of
contraception.

00:52:57.760 --> 00:53:03.385
When Fidel Ramos was President,
one of the early very populist

00:53:03.385 --> 00:53:06.539
president's,
he supported family planning

00:53:06.539 --> 00:53:10.077
and a quarter of the Filipino
women were using the modern

00:53:10.077 --> 00:53:10.710
method.
 

00:53:10.710 --> 00:53:15.340
Since then the desired
fertility has gone down in the

00:53:15.340 --> 00:53:20.773
Philippines and now more than
half of Filipino women want some

00:53:20.773 --> 00:53:23.090
form of birth control.
 

00:53:23.090 --> 00:53:26.869
But the presidency has changed
and a woman,

00:53:26.869 --> 00:53:30.965
Gloria Arroyo Macapagal,
came in and since Ferdinand

00:53:30.965 --> 00:53:36.106
Marcos was a strong dictator and
they had strong presidencies but

00:53:36.106 --> 00:53:39.697
then,
when he was kicked out for

00:53:39.697 --> 00:53:44.309
massive corruption and
dictatorial means,

00:53:44.309 --> 00:53:46.777
they now have democratic
elections and the governments

00:53:46.777 --> 00:53:47.849
have been quite weak.
 

00:53:47.849 --> 00:53:50.757
They don't have much popular
support and so the government

00:53:50.757 --> 00:53:53.766
needs to get legitimacy from
somewhere and in this case they

00:53:53.766 --> 00:53:56.469
get legitimacy from the Catholic
Church because,

00:53:56.469 --> 00:53:58.610
again, the Philippines is a
very Catholic country.

00:53:58.610 --> 00:54:02.952
A fairly open deal was made
between Macapagal and the

00:54:02.952 --> 00:54:08.047
archbishop of the Philippines
that the church will support you

00:54:08.047 --> 00:54:13.226
if you make abortion illegal and
get rid of the family planning

00:54:13.226 --> 00:54:14.480
programs.
 

00:54:14.480 --> 00:54:19.469
Now the government--and that
was taken and she got elected --

00:54:19.469 --> 00:54:23.476
and now the government only
supports the traditional family

00:54:23.476 --> 00:54:30.590
planning method,
which is withdrawal basically.

00:54:30.590 --> 00:54:31.670
This had an effect.
 

00:54:31.670 --> 00:54:35.900
So from 1993 to 1998 in the
five, six year period,

00:54:35.900 --> 00:54:40.737
the use of traditional methods
went up by 50% while the use of

00:54:40.737 --> 00:54:44.300
modern methods didn't--
actually didn't change much.

00:54:44.300 --> 00:54:49.059
When the government pushes
something it often goes up and

00:54:49.059 --> 00:54:53.650
all those traditional methods
just plain don't work.

00:54:53.650 --> 00:54:57.920
The result was that the number
of abortions in the Philippines

00:54:57.920 --> 00:55:02.190
in these years increased by 19%
from 400,000 which was already

00:55:02.190 --> 00:55:05.347
high--
from 400,000 it went up to

00:55:05.347 --> 00:55:08.940
basically a half a million
abortions.

00:55:08.940 --> 00:55:11.289
They're all illegal of course.
 

00:55:14.780 --> 00:55:19.206
As I said in the beginning,
in America abortion is a great

00:55:19.206 --> 00:55:21.070
source of controversy.
 

00:55:21.070 --> 00:55:24.764
This is not always the case in
a lot of places,

00:55:24.764 --> 00:55:29.181
so there's a lot of literature
now on what they call the

00:55:29.181 --> 00:55:31.110
culture of abortion.
 

00:55:31.110 --> 00:55:35.552
Those countries for whom
abortion has a non-controversial

00:55:35.552 --> 00:55:39.438
place as a mechanism for
fertility control just as

00:55:39.438 --> 00:55:44.199
contraception has a more or less
non-controversial place as a

00:55:44.199 --> 00:55:48.800
form of fertility control in say
Europe and America.

00:55:48.800 --> 00:55:54.190
I got invited a few years back
to talk to the women's health

00:55:54.190 --> 00:55:58.304
class about abortion and--
it was one of the things we

00:55:58.304 --> 00:56:00.934
talked about,
and afterwards I was talking

00:56:00.934 --> 00:56:04.273
with some students and a
professor with the next class

00:56:04.273 --> 00:56:08.307
walks in and he turned out to be
from Russia and he asked us what

00:56:08.307 --> 00:56:10.010
are you talking about?
 

00:56:10.010 --> 00:56:12.643
The students had started asking
me questions about--something

00:56:12.643 --> 00:56:13.389
about abortion.
 

00:56:13.389 --> 00:56:15.789
He was really puzzled;
he said 'abortion,

00:56:15.789 --> 00:56:17.250
why is anybody interested in
that?'

00:56:17.250 --> 00:56:20.985
Because in Russia it's just an
ordinary, absolutely ordinary

00:56:20.985 --> 00:56:23.420
kind of thing;
in places like Romania,

00:56:23.420 --> 00:56:26.820
and I'm sure this is to some
degree true in probably the

00:56:26.820 --> 00:56:28.489
whole of eastern Europe.
 

00:56:28.489 --> 00:56:32.188
Remember, I mentioned to you
the old theory that the health

00:56:32.188 --> 00:56:34.550
of the body depends on the
humors,

00:56:34.550 --> 00:56:37.590
that you've got four humors of
bile,

00:56:37.590 --> 00:56:40.097
and choler, and all this other
stuff and it's the balance

00:56:40.097 --> 00:56:40.949
that's important.
 

00:56:40.949 --> 00:56:44.150
You have to reestablish--What
the menstrual period does,

00:56:44.150 --> 00:56:46.590
everyone knows the worst fluid
is menstrual fluid,

00:56:46.590 --> 00:56:50.500
and so you've got to get rid of
that and if you don't--

00:56:50.500 --> 00:56:52.840
if you're not periodically
getting rid of menstrual fluid,

00:56:52.840 --> 00:56:57.985
the bad spirits humors,
fluids, build up in you and you

00:56:57.985 --> 00:56:59.510
get unhealthy.
 

00:56:59.510 --> 00:57:01.771
In places like Romania,
many people,

00:57:01.771 --> 00:57:05.456
older less educated people,
believe that it's good to have

00:57:05.456 --> 00:57:07.460
an abortion every so often.
 

00:57:07.460 --> 00:57:10.231
Having nothing to do with
pregnancy even,

00:57:10.231 --> 00:57:14.250
it's just good to do that to
get rid of this evil humor.

00:57:14.250 --> 00:57:19.007
That has persisted as well as a
lot of other really

00:57:19.007 --> 00:57:21.677
unbelievable--
almost unbelievable to us,

00:57:21.677 --> 00:57:24.150
medical myths and is part of
the reason for that very,

00:57:24.150 --> 00:57:28.099
very high abortion rate in
Romania.

00:57:28.099 --> 00:57:31.527
In the Ukraine,
when the Soviet Union fell

00:57:31.527 --> 00:57:33.851
apart,
the family planning programs

00:57:33.851 --> 00:57:38.373
that they had also fell apart,
and so the whole area was left

00:57:38.373 --> 00:57:41.550
without effective family
planning.

00:57:41.550 --> 00:57:44.396
The International Planned
Parenthood Federation,

00:57:44.396 --> 00:57:47.728
their nearest office was in
Bangkok and so they couldn't

00:57:47.728 --> 00:57:48.880
help very much.
 

00:57:48.880 --> 00:57:51.601
What they did is,
they said, we'll take just the

00:57:51.601 --> 00:57:55.019
city of Moscow because it's most
cost effective to work in a

00:57:55.019 --> 00:57:56.384
city,
a lot of people,

00:57:56.384 --> 00:57:58.050
we don't have geographic
access,

00:57:58.050 --> 00:58:00.969
but, we'll try to provide some
contraception in Moscow.

00:58:00.969 --> 00:58:03.949
That left all the other Soviet
Bloc countries with nothing.

00:58:03.949 --> 00:58:07.090
The Planned Parenthood
Federation of Connecticut here,

00:58:07.090 --> 00:58:08.820
I was associated with them at
the time,

00:58:08.820 --> 00:58:12.445
got in contact with the
Ukraine--the whole Ukraine was

00:58:12.445 --> 00:58:14.909
left like bereft of
contraception.

00:58:14.909 --> 00:58:20.699
Got in touch with the main--the
head and the university in Kiev,

00:58:20.699 --> 00:58:24.239
the head of the OB/GYN
Department, a very nice woman,

00:58:24.239 --> 00:58:29.478
and started to help her
provide--buy contraceptives here

00:58:29.478 --> 00:58:31.670
and ship them abroad.
 

00:58:31.670 --> 00:58:33.784
Actually we buy them
internationally,

00:58:33.784 --> 00:58:37.250
very cheap, a cycle of pills is
$.80 on the world market.

00:58:37.250 --> 00:58:42.659
A condom is like a penny and a
half, diaphragm is $1.25.

00:58:42.659 --> 00:58:45.190
So, if you buy them in the
United States they're expensive.

00:58:45.190 --> 00:58:47.905
If you buy them in India or
wherever they're made,

00:58:47.905 --> 00:58:50.954
the things are a lot of
cheaper, so we could really help

00:58:50.954 --> 00:58:51.619
Ukraine.
 

00:58:51.619 --> 00:58:54.849
What they wanted first
was--because you can't use any

00:58:54.849 --> 00:58:58.452
of these things if there's
pelvic infections so they wanted

00:58:58.452 --> 00:59:01.931
Monistat and other treatments
for vaginal infections as a

00:59:01.931 --> 00:59:04.913
first line and than they could
start dealing with

00:59:04.913 --> 00:59:06.280
contraception.
 

00:59:06.280 --> 00:59:09.811
Anyway, this program went on
but it wasn't very successful

00:59:09.811 --> 00:59:12.784
and the reason was,
the women were using abortion

00:59:12.784 --> 00:59:14.829
and were quite happy with it.
 

00:59:14.829 --> 00:59:17.000
They didn't see anything wrong
with it;

00:59:17.000 --> 00:59:18.860
they were used to it,
and no problems,

00:59:18.860 --> 00:59:20.170
so why should we change?
 

00:59:20.170 --> 00:59:24.239
One of the things that they
did, and we helped them,

00:59:24.239 --> 00:59:27.690
was we got some of these
right-to-life films,

00:59:27.690 --> 00:59:31.250
which show, in the goriest way,
what the fetus looks like and

00:59:31.250 --> 00:59:34.809
what an abortion is like and you
know are really are way,

00:59:34.809 --> 00:59:37.175
way off the deep end and
shipped them to them so they

00:59:37.175 --> 00:59:38.860
could show their patients and
say,

00:59:38.860 --> 00:59:43.719
'see an abortion is not just
this sort of nothing kind of

00:59:43.719 --> 00:59:44.500
event.'
 

