The most interesting case might
be Cuba which has one of the

00:59:49.159 --> 00:59:52.239
highest abortion rates in the
world,

00:59:52.239 --> 00:59:57.297
78 per 1,000 women per year,
compared to Canada which has

00:59:57.297 --> 00:59:58.974
15.5,
for instance,

00:59:58.974 --> 01:00:02.570
again that's the two sides of
the United States.

01:00:02.570 --> 01:00:08.090
Almost 60% of what they call
known pregnancies are terminated

01:00:08.090 --> 01:00:09.380
by abortion.
 

01:00:09.380 --> 01:00:10.920
So they have a long history.
 

01:00:10.920 --> 01:00:14.684
Before 1938 they were very much
tied culturally to Spain,

01:00:14.684 --> 01:00:16.969
and Spain was very
conservative.

01:00:16.969 --> 01:00:21.266
That was the Franco era;
a very, very right wing

01:00:21.266 --> 01:00:24.389
fascist, Catholic dictatorship
and so--

01:00:24.389 --> 01:00:26.929
in the Spanish law all forms of
abortion,

01:00:26.929 --> 01:00:31.606
induced abortion were illegal,
and Cuba just used that same

01:00:31.606 --> 01:00:32.090
law.
 

01:00:32.090 --> 01:00:36.710
It was up until 1938,
and in 1938 they liberalized a

01:00:36.710 --> 01:00:40.880
little bit for rape,
likelihood of death of the

01:00:40.880 --> 01:00:45.230
mother, or severe fetal
malformation issues.

01:00:45.230 --> 01:00:48.971
Despite these restrictions it
was the mechanism of birth

01:00:48.971 --> 01:00:52.713
control in Cuba and it was used
widely by all the social

01:00:52.713 --> 01:00:53.530
classes.
 

01:00:53.530 --> 01:00:55.614
Well, I'll tell you an
exception to that,

01:00:55.614 --> 01:00:58.635
and by poor people and it was
used in the cities and in the

01:00:58.635 --> 01:00:59.469
countryside.
 

01:00:59.469 --> 01:01:01.849
So abortion was it.
 

01:01:01.849 --> 01:01:07.141
Contraception starts coming in
but it's a foreign product and

01:01:07.141 --> 01:01:09.666
it's expensive,
and you need some medical

01:01:09.666 --> 01:01:12.952
knowledge to use it,
so only the upper class uses

01:01:12.952 --> 01:01:15.449
contraception,
at this time,

01:01:15.449 --> 01:01:17.800
used contraception in Cuba.
 

01:01:17.800 --> 01:01:20.568
At that time a very,
very--few people owned all the

01:01:20.568 --> 01:01:23.835
sugar plantations and everyone
else was basically a slave on

01:01:23.835 --> 01:01:26.894
the sugar plantations,
so the social gulf between the

01:01:26.894 --> 01:01:29.818
rich people using contraception
and the poor people using

01:01:29.818 --> 01:01:32.949
abortion was enormous and they
didn't talk to each other.

01:01:32.949 --> 01:01:36.927
So there was no social
diffusion of the ideas of

01:01:36.927 --> 01:01:40.481
contraception,
so the people just continued

01:01:40.481 --> 01:01:42.090
using abortion.
 

01:01:42.090 --> 01:01:47.079
1959 Fidel Castro has his
revolution and he takes over,

01:01:47.079 --> 01:01:51.570
and in the beginning he's
anti-abortion,

01:01:51.570 --> 01:01:54.436
he still is,
and a lot of events happened

01:01:54.436 --> 01:01:57.590
and I'm simplifying a
complicated history.

01:01:57.590 --> 01:02:00.623
By 1962 the United States
places an embargo on Cuba,

01:02:00.623 --> 01:02:04.074
including medical supplies,
and guess what the Cubans can't

01:02:04.074 --> 01:02:04.550
get?
 

01:02:04.550 --> 01:02:07.693
Contraception,
because the United States was

01:02:07.693 --> 01:02:10.911
their source of supply,
so abortion gets more

01:02:10.911 --> 01:02:12.010
entrenched.
 

01:02:12.010 --> 01:02:16.025
The embargo might have done the
biggest thing to raise Cuban

01:02:16.025 --> 01:02:19.876
rates;
no one has good statistics on

01:02:19.876 --> 01:02:20.559
that.
 

01:02:20.559 --> 01:02:25.615
While abortion is legal in
Cuba, the government really

01:02:25.615 --> 01:02:27.619
wants to reduce it.
 

01:02:27.619 --> 01:02:31.405
In 1998 the Pope visited Cuba
as you probably may remember

01:02:31.405 --> 01:02:35.190
from all the headlines and he
talked against abortion,

01:02:35.190 --> 01:02:37.925
then, shortly after that,
Castro gave a seven hour

01:02:37.925 --> 01:02:39.449
lecture,
worse than me,

01:02:39.449 --> 01:02:43.353
a seven hour lecture condemning
abortion as a method of birth

01:02:43.353 --> 01:02:44.070
control.
 

01:02:44.070 --> 01:02:47.585
He said it was his duty as a
public figure and a

01:02:47.585 --> 01:02:51.550
revolutionary leader to oppose
widespread abortion.

01:02:51.550 --> 01:02:54.768
It didn't have any effect on
the people,

01:02:54.768 --> 01:02:58.070
and it's very interesting,
there is now a wonderful

01:02:58.070 --> 01:03:01.831
article which I actually should
have assigned to you about

01:03:01.831 --> 01:03:03.679
what's going on in Cuba.
 

01:03:03.679 --> 01:03:06.900
You have too much reading
already.

01:03:06.900 --> 01:03:11.016
The medical--the government and
the medical establishment want

01:03:11.016 --> 01:03:13.849
to get people--wean people off
abortion.

01:03:13.849 --> 01:03:16.539
In these interviews one of the
things they ask the respondents,

01:03:16.539 --> 01:03:19.929
who are women of all ages and
men of all ages,

01:03:19.929 --> 01:03:23.728
'well what have you heard from
doctors and healthcare

01:03:23.728 --> 01:03:24.969
professionals.'
 

01:03:24.969 --> 01:03:28.679
'Well that's it's dangerous,
that you can die from it.

01:03:28.679 --> 01:03:31.068
Just imagine'--that's what
she's heard from the

01:03:31.068 --> 01:03:34.289
professionals--'but just imagine
if you had to give birth every

01:03:34.289 --> 01:03:35.639
time you got pregnant.
 

01:03:35.639 --> 01:03:38.654
I got pregnant and had an
abortion when I was 15 even

01:03:38.654 --> 01:03:40.219
though I was on the pill.
 

01:03:40.219 --> 01:03:43.570
I also got pregnant earlier
when I was using an IUD.'

01:03:43.570 --> 01:03:45.835
This was a woman,
who at the time of the

01:03:45.835 --> 01:03:48.797
interview was age 30,
and she had--this is after her

01:03:48.797 --> 01:03:49.960
fourth abortion.
 

01:03:49.960 --> 01:03:53.541
The people's perception is very
different than what they're

01:03:53.541 --> 01:03:56.998
hearing from the medical
establishment and the government

01:03:56.998 --> 01:03:58.110
establishment.
 

01:03:58.110 --> 01:04:03.250
It's an absolutely unremarkable
subject for discussion.

01:04:03.250 --> 01:04:07.186
One male who is now age 49
said, 'I was about ten

01:04:07.186 --> 01:04:12.190
years'--they ask what have
you--do you hear about abortion?

01:04:12.190 --> 01:04:13.099
Is it discussed?
 

01:04:13.099 --> 01:04:17.559
He says, 'sure,
I was about ten years old,

01:04:17.559 --> 01:04:20.130
I heard about abortion from
people on the street,

01:04:20.130 --> 01:04:24.054
also in my house my mom talked
about it with her friends in

01:04:24.054 --> 01:04:25.070
front of me.'
 

01:04:25.070 --> 01:04:28.074
Another respondent:
'Around the streets abortion is

01:04:28.074 --> 01:04:30.179
a common thing people talk
about.

01:04:30.179 --> 01:04:31.389
It's an everyday thing.'
 

01:04:31.389 --> 01:04:35.018
A male aged 23.
 

01:04:35.018 --> 01:04:38.789
"Do you know anyone in
your family, among your friends

01:04:38.789 --> 01:04:40.739
who's had an abortion?"
 

01:04:40.739 --> 01:04:42.369
'Yes, an aunt of mine.'
 

01:04:42.369 --> 01:04:43.340
"What did she tell
you?"

01:04:43.340 --> 01:04:45.929
'That you don't feel anything,
that they give you the

01:04:45.929 --> 01:04:48.219
anesthetic and stuff,
everything goes fine.'

01:04:48.219 --> 01:04:52.150
That was a woman of 18 who's
just had her first abortion.

01:04:52.150 --> 01:04:54.373
Another respondent,
'yes friends of mine,

01:04:54.373 --> 01:04:57.541
they told me that they had it
done and that you don't feel

01:04:57.541 --> 01:04:58.320
anything.'
 

01:04:58.320 --> 01:05:02.190
Now that was a 15 year old girl
with her first abortion.

01:05:02.190 --> 01:05:04.440
Another respondent,
'my cousin had an abortion,

01:05:04.440 --> 01:05:07.032
she told me that nothing out of
the ordinary happened,

01:05:07.032 --> 01:05:08.550
that everything went well.'
 

01:05:08.550 --> 01:05:11.800
This is a female aged 21 on her
second abortion.

01:05:11.800 --> 01:05:13.541
Another respondent,
'when I was in school,

01:05:13.541 --> 01:05:15.030
a friend of mine had an
abortion;

01:05:15.030 --> 01:05:18.416
she was fairly young around 13
years old because we were in the

01:05:18.416 --> 01:05:19.289
eighth grade.'
 

01:05:19.289 --> 01:05:21.590
"What did she tell you,
how did it go?"

01:05:21.590 --> 01:05:25.177
'She told me it went well and
said the anesthetic was fine,

01:05:25.177 --> 01:05:27.590
girls talk about that kind of
stuff.'

01:05:27.590 --> 01:05:33.199
This was a 31 year old woman on
her fourth abortion.

01:05:33.199 --> 01:05:36.228
Another respondent--to the
question, have you heard much

01:05:36.228 --> 01:05:37.440
talk about abortion?
 

01:05:37.440 --> 01:05:39.030
'Oh yes, among girls at school.
 

01:05:39.030 --> 01:05:41.186
They don't use anything,'
meaning they don't use any

01:05:41.186 --> 01:05:43.090
contraceptives,
'so when they get pregnant the

01:05:43.090 --> 01:05:44.190
go to get an abortion.
 

01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:46.139
They talk about it like it's
nothing;

01:05:46.139 --> 01:05:47.929
it's like drinking a glass of
water.

01:05:47.929 --> 01:05:50.958
Some people have problems when
they get an abortion but most

01:05:50.958 --> 01:05:51.730
people don't.
 

01:05:51.730 --> 01:05:54.530
Almost always the procedure
goes fine.'

01:05:54.530 --> 01:05:59.570
That's a 17 year old girl after
her first abortion.

01:05:59.570 --> 01:06:03.496
It's a very interesting case
because while they're

01:06:03.496 --> 01:06:05.625
experienced,
they're hearing one thing from

01:06:05.625 --> 01:06:07.403
the government,
the same thing from the medical

01:06:07.403 --> 01:06:09.793
community but they know lots and
lots of people who have had

01:06:09.793 --> 01:06:11.137
abortions,
a common subject,

01:06:11.137 --> 01:06:13.750
and they're not hearing about
any difficulties from it,

01:06:13.750 --> 01:06:15.559
or very rarely are they.
 

01:06:15.559 --> 01:06:18.766
The government's pushing
contraception and they use

01:06:18.766 --> 01:06:21.394
contraception,
92% of the Cuban women have

01:06:21.394 --> 01:06:22.869
used contraception.
 

01:06:22.869 --> 01:06:26.835
That's some time--even among
adolescent girls who are

01:06:26.835 --> 01:06:31.411
obviously having a very rich sex
life because they're getting

01:06:31.411 --> 01:06:36.525
pregnant all the time,
84% have used some form of

01:06:36.525 --> 01:06:38.289
contraception.
 

01:06:38.289 --> 01:06:41.413
It doesn't mean anything to
them, because they're just as

01:06:41.413 --> 01:06:42.639
happy with abortion.
 

01:06:42.639 --> 01:06:45.478
So, they're not worried about
getting pregnant so they

01:06:45.478 --> 01:06:48.411
sometimes use contraception,
they sometimes don't,

01:06:48.411 --> 01:06:51.621
and the reports of when they
use it are almost totally

01:06:51.621 --> 01:06:52.409
haphazard.
 

01:06:52.409 --> 01:06:54.601
They'll use it for a while,
they'll stop using it,

01:06:54.601 --> 01:06:56.659
they'll start again and they
change methods.

01:06:56.659 --> 01:07:00.925
It doesn't even have any--of
course women go through periods

01:07:00.925 --> 01:07:03.494
and men too,
when they're in a relationship

01:07:03.494 --> 01:07:05.869
having sex or just having a lot
of casual sex,

01:07:05.869 --> 01:07:08.608
and the woman will tell you
this and the use of

01:07:08.608 --> 01:07:12.121
contraception did not correlate
at all with periods when the

01:07:12.121 --> 01:07:13.670
women were having sex.
 

01:07:13.670 --> 01:07:17.293
It's just a total disconnect
and undoubtedly the reason is

01:07:17.293 --> 01:07:20.916
that they're perfectly happy
with abortion and it's a fine

01:07:20.916 --> 01:07:24.668
backup so they don't have to be
terribly careful about using

01:07:24.668 --> 01:07:25.940
contraception.
 

01:07:25.940 --> 01:07:32.007
In fact, much as they're
hearing that abortion is no big

01:07:32.007 --> 01:07:34.918
deal,
they're hearing that the other

01:07:34.918 --> 01:07:38.909
forms of other contraception are
really not very pleasant.

01:07:38.909 --> 01:07:41.730
Here are more answers to survey
questions.

01:07:41.730 --> 01:07:45.655
'I don't like the pill because
of extra hormones in the woman's

01:07:45.655 --> 01:07:47.809
body,' a male aged 19 says that.
 

01:07:47.809 --> 01:07:50.983
This is a woman:
'No, I don't use any IUD

01:07:50.983 --> 01:07:53.760
because my body can't support
it.

01:07:53.760 --> 01:07:55.210
It falls out of place.'
 

01:07:55.210 --> 01:07:57.590
"You have used an IUD in
the past?"

01:07:57.590 --> 01:08:00.766
'Yes, I had an IUD two
different times and both times

01:08:00.766 --> 01:08:01.989
it fell out place.
 

01:08:01.989 --> 01:08:03.869
I have problems with IUDs.'
 

01:08:03.869 --> 01:08:08.409
That's a 37 year old woman on
her second abortion.

01:08:08.409 --> 01:08:11.719
IUD causes pain to women.
 

01:08:11.719 --> 01:08:14.423
'After my first pregnancy I had
an IUD inserted,

01:08:14.423 --> 01:08:17.819
but I had to have it removed
because it was causing pain.

01:08:17.819 --> 01:08:21.337
I started having problems with
my period and a lot of

01:08:21.337 --> 01:08:24.154
inflammation,
and when I had sex it was

01:08:24.154 --> 01:08:27.831
painful, so I had the IUD
removed,' female aged 35 her

01:08:27.831 --> 01:08:29.078
first abortion.
 

01:08:29.078 --> 01:08:32.292
'I had an IUD before,
I had it for two years,

01:08:32.292 --> 01:08:36.091
but I had it removed because I
had abnormal menstrual

01:08:36.091 --> 01:08:39.890
bleeding,' a 42 year old woman,
fourth abortion.

01:08:39.890 --> 01:08:42.463
Another woman,
'sometimes I'll use protection

01:08:42.463 --> 01:08:43.810
but the condom broke.
 

01:08:43.810 --> 01:08:47.131
You explain these things to the
doctors and they say that--this

01:08:47.131 --> 01:08:49.920
doesn't happen but I'm telling
you it's not a lie.

01:08:49.920 --> 01:08:53.948
Sometimes condoms are bad and
they break,' a 19 year old girl

01:08:53.948 --> 01:08:55.560
on her third abortion.
 

01:09:00.658 --> 01:09:04.586
At the time of the survey 88%
were practicing contraception at

01:09:04.586 --> 01:09:07.752
the time of the survey,
and again, among adolescents

01:09:07.752 --> 01:09:10.420
68% were using condoms at the
time of the survey.

01:09:10.420 --> 01:09:13.743
Yet, the contraception,
they didn't like it,

01:09:13.743 --> 01:09:17.532
it wasn't effective,
and they were apparently just

01:09:17.532 --> 01:09:19.619
as happy with abortion.
 

01:09:27.908 --> 01:09:31.382
It's a very interesting thing
and this is repeated in

01:09:31.382 --> 01:09:34.590
basically all of the east
European countries,

01:09:34.590 --> 01:09:37.456
where again,
they have long experience with

01:09:37.456 --> 01:09:41.140
abortion and they don't
particularly see any benefit to

01:09:41.140 --> 01:09:42.368
contraception.
 

01:09:42.368 --> 01:09:46.036
Now the standard thing that
you'll hear in America from

01:09:46.036 --> 01:09:49.907
everybody, independent of
their--they can be right to life

01:09:49.907 --> 01:09:51.130
or pro-choice.
 

01:09:51.130 --> 01:09:55.382
Their thing is that--the idea
is, and I've been sort of saying

01:09:55.382 --> 01:09:58.340
that here,
the idea is to replace abortion

01:09:58.340 --> 01:10:01.815
with contraception,
that contraception is a better

01:10:01.815 --> 01:10:04.529
method of birth control than
abortion.

01:10:04.529 --> 01:10:07.899
It's controversial--but now
it's controversial.

01:10:07.899 --> 01:10:10.497
Actually, what started me
really looking into this was a

01:10:10.497 --> 01:10:12.670
number of years ago I was giving
a lecture,

01:10:12.670 --> 01:10:16.421
and I was saying very overtly,
that well it's progress when

01:10:16.421 --> 01:10:18.618
contraception replaces abortion.
 

01:10:18.618 --> 01:10:26.235
Now it's not so obvious because
I showed you this one,

01:10:26.235 --> 01:10:34.140
that the safest method is
condoms backed by abortion.

01:10:34.140 --> 01:10:37.971
It's very--it was very
hard--one student asked me this

01:10:37.971 --> 01:10:40.869
question about why is--
why do you think that

01:10:40.869 --> 01:10:43.779
contraception is better than
abortion and it's a very,

01:10:43.779 --> 01:10:48.525
very hard question to answer
and I won't even try to do this

01:10:48.525 --> 01:10:49.170
today.
 

01:10:49.170 --> 01:10:52.350
It's a very difficult kind of
issue.

01:10:52.350 --> 01:10:56.065
The final thing that I should
tell you is that one of the

01:10:56.065 --> 01:10:59.649
things we worry about is the
population growth rate.

01:10:59.649 --> 01:11:03.643
Abortion makes a huge
difference in the global rate of

01:11:03.643 --> 01:11:05.149
population growth.
 

01:11:05.149 --> 01:11:08.822
As I told you,
there's ballpark 75 million

01:11:08.822 --> 01:11:11.328
increase in the world now.
 

01:11:11.328 --> 01:11:16.381
If the abortion rate is about
somewhere between 40 and 50

01:11:16.381 --> 01:11:21.884
million, that means the rate of
world population increase goes

01:11:21.884 --> 01:11:24.319
up by 75% or something.
 

01:11:24.319 --> 01:11:27.859
Because abortion is such a
large fraction of the birthrate,

01:11:27.859 --> 01:11:31.069
if abortion disappears and is
not replaced by contraception,

01:11:31.069 --> 01:11:34.408
the population growth rate goes
crazy.

01:11:34.408 --> 01:11:37.060
In the world,
as it is now,

01:11:37.060 --> 01:11:43.378
there's probably not any chance
of stabilizing world population

01:11:43.378 --> 01:11:45.520
without abortion.
 

01:11:45.520 --> 01:11:48.930
Just on time,
we will continue with the

01:11:48.930 --> 01:11:54.318
biology of abortion and some of
the history and philosophical

01:11:54.318 --> 01:11:57.819
considerations in the next
lecture.

